1 packet Creamy Pesto Dressing
1 Cos Lettuce
2 Kumara
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 Cucumber
1 packet Sriracha
2 Brioche Hotdog Buns
1 Lemon
200 g Peeled Prawns
1 packet Parsley
20 g butter
¼ cup white wine vinegar
1 drizzle olive oil

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut orange kūmara into 0.5cm-thick rounds.
• Place kūmara on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with garlic & herb
seasoning, season with pepper and toss to coat.
• Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide the kūmara
between two trays.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber into rounds.
Trim end of cos lettuce (see ingredients) and
separate leaves. Roughly chop parsley. Slice
lemon into wedges.
• In a medium bowl, combine the white wine
vinegar and a good pinch of sugar and salt.
• Add cucumber to pickling liquid. Add enough
water to just cover cucumber. Set aside.

• When kūmara has 10 minutes remaining, heat
a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan over
medium-high heat.
• Cook peeled prawns, tossing, until pink and
starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes.
• Transfer cooked prawns onto a chopping board,
then roughly chop. Allow to cool slightly.

• In a second medium bowl, combine creamy
pesto dressing, a generous squeeze of lemon
juice, sriracha and parsley.
• Add cooked prawns, tossing to coat. Season
with salt and pepper.

• Slice brioche hotdog buns in half lengthways.
• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium heat
with the butter. Toast bread, open side down,
until golden, 1-2 minutes.

• Drain pickled cucumber.
• Assemble rolls with some pickled cucumber, cos
and prawn mixture.
• Divide creamy prawn brioche rolls between
plates. Serve with kūmara rounds and any
remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!